  "text": "Agmon et al., [CITATION_1] showed that vitD inhibited in vitro the expression of tissue factor induced by aB2GPI antibodies, therefore exerting an anti-thrombotic effect. However in our study vit D was measured at a time that was not necessarily the time of thrombosis, thus, many other factors can interfere the results. The association of vitamin D and thrombosis should be assessed in well-designed studies and also at the time of the thrombotic event.",
